"Wang W., Dai J.R., Liang Y.S., Huang Y.X., Coles G.C.","Impact of the South-to-North water diversion project on the transmission of Schistosoma japonicum in China",2009,"Annals of Tropical Medicine and Parasitology","103","1",,"17","29",,,10.1179/136485909X384974,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-58849141702&partnerID=40&md5=daa758b612a3ecb0b705e24e2ac0fca7","Jiangsu Institute of Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China; Key Laboratory on Technology for Parasitic Disease Prevention and Control, Ministry of Health, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China; Jiangsu Provincial Key Laboratory on Molecular Biology of Parasites, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China; Jiangsu Provincial Key Subject on Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China; School of Clinical Veterinary Science, University of Bristol, Langford House, Bristol BS40 5DU, United Kingdom; Jiangsu Institute of Parasitic Diseases, Melyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China","Wang, W., Jiangsu Institute of Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Key Laboratory on Technology for Parasitic Disease Prevention and Control, Ministry of Health, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Provincial Key Laboratory on Molecular Biology of Parasites, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Provincial Key Subject on Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China; Dai, J.R., Jiangsu Institute of Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Key Laboratory on Technology for Parasitic Disease Prevention and Control, Ministry of Health, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Provincial Key Laboratory on Molecular Biology of Parasites, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Provincial Key Subject on Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China; Liang, Y.S., Jiangsu Institute of Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Key Laboratory on Technology for Parasitic Disease Prevention and Control, Ministry of Health, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Provincial Key Laboratory on Molecular Biology of Parasites, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Provincial Key Subject on Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Institute of Parasitic Diseases, Melyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China; Huang, Y.X., Jiangsu Institute of Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Key Laboratory on Technology for Parasitic Disease Prevention and Control, Ministry of Health, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Provincial Key Laboratory on Molecular Biology of Parasites, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China, Jiangsu Provincial Key Subject on Parasitic Diseases, Meiyuan, Yangxiang 117, Wuxi 214064, Jiangsu Province, China; Coles, G.C., School of Clinical Veterinary Science, University of Bristol, Langford House, Bristol BS40 5DU, United Kingdom","The South-to-North Water Diversion Project (SNWDP) is currently the key, national, water-conservation project in China, designed to optimise the use of water resources and relieve the water shortages in the north of the country. As one of the main water intakes for the project, that of the Eastern Route Scheme (ERS), is a breeding site for Oncomelania hupensis (the intermediate host of Schistosoma japonicum), there is concern that the snail may be carried far to the north, in the water passing through the project. To see if they could survive and breed to the north of their current range in China, O. hupensis were collected in marshland near Nanjing City and transferred to cages, on the banks offish ponds, in the cities of Zhenjiang (in Jiangsu province, at 32°10'N), Xuzhou (in the same province but at a latitude of 34°23'N) and Jining (in Shandong province, at 35°23'N). Except over the first 6 months in Xuzhou, the snails moved north of their natural distribution did not survive and reproduce as well as those in Zhenjiang, and all those transferred to Jining died out within 1 year. Although the snail populations in Xuzhou survived for 7-8 years and retained their infectivity to S. japonicum, histological and histochemical studies revealed abnormalities in the reproductive organs of these snails. It is concluded that, unless global warming significantly increases the minimum winter temperatures in northern China, the SNWDP is unlikely to result in the northward spread of schistosomiasis japonica. © The Liverpool School of Tropical Medicine 2009.",,"animal tissue; article; breeding; China; fluid intake; greenhouse effect; intermediate host; nonhuman; parasite incidence; parasite migration; parasite survival; parasite transmission; parasite vector; pond; Schistosoma japonicum; schistosomiasis japonica; snail; water supply; winter; Animals; China; Disease Vectors; Female; Fresh Water; Humans; Male; Models, Theoretical; Parasite Egg Count; Schistosoma japonicum; Schistosomiasis japonica; Seasons; Snails; Temperature; Water Supply; Gastropoda; Japonica; Oncomelania hupensis; Schistosoma japonicum",,,,,,"(2000) Handbook of Schistosomiasis Control, , Shanghai, China: Shanghai Science and Technology Press. Anon; Audibert, M., Josseran, R., Josse, R., Adjidji, A., Irrigation, schistosomiasis, and malaria in the Logone Valley, Cameroon (1990) American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene, 42, pp. 550-560; Chayen, J., Bitensky, Z., Butcher, R.G., (1973) Practical Histochemistry, , New York, NY: John Wiley & Sons; Chen, X.Y., Wang, L.Y., Cai, J.M., Zhou,