, Y.S., Impact of project diverting Yangtze River water to Northern Jiangsu on transmission towards north of Oncomelania hupensis snails (2005) Chinese Journal of Schistosomiasis Control, 17, pp. 184-189; Huang, Y.X., Gao, Y., Hong, Q.B., Sun, L.P., Yang, K., Li, W., Zhang, J.F., Liang, Y.S., Observation on Oncomelania hupensis spread in Jiangdu pumping station in the east route of South-North Water Diversion Project (2006) Chinese Journal of Schistosomiasis Control, 18, pp. 247-251; Huang, Y.X., Xu, Z.K., Ren, Z.Y., Tian, Z.Z., Yang, Z., Gao, Y., Hong, Q.B., Liang, Y.S., (2007) Impact of water flow on transmission towards north of Oncomelania hupensis after the first phase of the east route of; Chinese Journal of Schistosomiasis Control, 19, pp. 91-97. , South-to-North Water Diversion Project; Hunter, J.M., Rey, L., Scott, D., Man-made lakes and man-made diseases. Towards a policy resolution (1982) Social Science and Medicine, 16, pp. 1127-1145; Khalil, M., The national campaign for the treatment and control of bilharziasis for the scientific and economic aspects (1949) Journal of the Royal Egyptian Medical Association, 32, pp. 817-856; Li, F.J., Anatomy and Comparative Anatomy of Oncomelania (1956) Snail, , Wuhan, China: Hubei People's Press; Mao, C.P., (1990) Biology of Schistosome and Control of Schistosomiasis, , Beijing: People's Medical Publishing House; Nachlas, M.M., Tsou, K.C., de Souza, E., Cheng, C.S., Seligman, A.M., Cytochemical demonstration of succinic dehydrogenase by the use of a new p-nitrophenyl substituted ditetrazole (1957) Journal of Histochemistry and Cytochemistry, 5, pp. 420-436; Ofoezie, I.E., Human health and sustainable water resources development in Nigeria: Schistosomiasis in artificial lakes (2002) Natural Resources Forum, 26, pp. 150-160; Oladejo, S.O., Ofoezie, I.E., Unabated schistosomiasis transmission in Erinle River dam, Osun state, Nigeria: Evidence of neglect of environmental effects of development projects (2006) Tropical Med